  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Saving Rhinos with Solar Energy</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kenya&apos;s Ol Pejeta Conservancy is the largest black rhino sanctuary in East Africa. Ol Pejeta has made a commitment to ONLY be using renewable energy by 2023. This task begins with the conversion of our diesel-powered boreholes to solar. Each borehole once converted to solar - we have 10 of them - will save US$7,000 per year in fuel. All our savings from going solar will be put straight back into wildlife conservation and community development.  By going solar, we save rhinos!</narrative>
  </description>
